{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pullrequests/38/comments/40349138.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-common:03488761daf8..1b1b783cdbe1?path=src%2FWorkerPool.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pull-requests/38/_/diff#comment-40349138"}}, "parent": {"id": 40327627, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pullrequests/38/comments/40327627.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pull-requests/38/_/diff#comment-40327627"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 38, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pullrequests/38.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pull-requests/38"}}, "title": "Thread/Worker pool"}, "content": {"raw": "I think I'm wrong about this check, and should remove it. `WorkerPool` doesn't have copy or move constructors, so it can't be copied or moved. The implicit copy constructor is deleted because `std::unique_ptr` copy constructor is deleted, and the implicit move constructor is deleted because there is a declared destructor. I don't see a path to making `dataPtr` null.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I think I'm wrong about this check, and should remove it. <code>WorkerPool</code> doesn't have copy or move constructors, so it can't be copied or moved. The implicit copy constructor is deleted because <code>std::unique_ptr</code> copy constructor is deleted, and the implicit move constructor is deleted because there is a declared destructor. I don't see a path to making <code>dataPtr</code> null.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-07-08T00:14:33.499517+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Shane Loretz", "uuid": "{656e3311-aad9-45a1-aaf7-b0ee0e84b287}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B656e3311-aad9-45a1-aaf7-b0ee0e84b287%7D"}, "h